        <!-- FAQ -->
        <section class="content-section">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>PNC Statement Converter FAQ</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Does it work with PNC Virtual Wallet statements?</h3>
                    <p>Yes! Our converter is specifically designed to handle PNC's unique Virtual Wallet statements. It intelligently separates transactions from your Spend, Reserve, and Growth accounts while maintaining the relationships between them. You'll get clean, organized data for each sub-account.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Can I convert PNC business account statements?</h3>
                    <p>Absolutely. We support all PNC business account types including Business Checking, Business Checking Plus, Treasury Management accounts, and Merchant Services statements. Our converter handles complex business transactions including ACH batches and wire transfers.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>How far back can I convert PNC statements?</h3>
                    <p>You can convert any PNC PDF statement regardless of age. While PNC provides 18 months of statements online, if you have older PDFs saved, our converter will process them perfectly. The format recognition works for statements dating back several years.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Does it preserve PNC's spending categories?</h3>
                    <p>Yes, all PNC transaction categories and merchant information are preserved in the conversion. This includes PNC's automatic categorization for Virtual Wallet users and any custom categories you've assigned in online banking.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What about PNC credit card statements?</h3>
                    <p>Our converter handles all PNC credit card statements including Cash Rewards, Points, Core, and business credit cards. It preserves reward point transactions, cash back details, and payment information.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Is it secure for sensitive banking data?</h3>
                    <p>Security is our top priority. We use bank-level 256-bit SSL encryption, process files in isolated environments, and automatically delete all uploaded files after conversion. We never store your statements or financial data.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Can I convert multiple PNC statements at once?</h3>
                    <p>Currently, statements are converted one at a time for security reasons. For businesses needing batch processing of multiple PNC statements, we offer API access with volume pricing. Contact us for details.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What if my PNC statement is password protected?</h3>
                    <p>You'll need to remove the password protection before uploading. Open the PDF in Adobe Reader or Preview, enter your password, then save a copy without password protection. This is a one-time step for each statement.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
